                        syriaca-computed-end="0435">0412-0435</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl26-1">AMS, IV, 396- 450 ; BHO, 1023. Suhada ', II, 339- 54 ; cf. Peeters, RHPO, I, 139-70. Sur ses reuvres : Barsaum, Lu'lu '2 , 258-60. Sur sa doctrine : DTC, XIII, col. 162Q-26 (1. Ziade). G.G. Blum, Rabbula von Edessa. Der Christ, der Bischof, der Th eolog (Louvain, 1969; CSCO 300, Subsidia 34). F. Nau, "Les 'belles actions' de Mar Rabboula, eveque d'Edesse, de 412 au 7 aout 435 ou 436", RHR 103 (1931), 97- 135. BSO, II, 869- 70 (J .M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Rabula was the bishop of Edessa.  He was the son of a rich pagan.  As bishop of Edessa, he lived an ascetic life, helped the poor, and fought heretics.  </note>
